This month, we would normally be encouraging engaging ways to promote awareness for childhood cancer and raise funds to support cancer research. However, with the social restrictions we are facing now in the midst of the pandemic, we need to get creative with the ways we can help join together in the fight against childhood cancer.

What are some unique ways that you and your children can help be a friend to someone you may know battling cancer? Can you send cards or letters to a local hospital? How about sending a meal to a family going through this battle? What about knitting blankets or hats to help keep them warm while undergoing chemotherapy?

We‚Äôll check in later this month to see what your family was able to do, but let‚Äôs hear some of your ideas below.
